-- Egypt, Libya Agree on Anti-Smuggling Effort on Border Crossings
-- B y   A b d e l   L a t i f   W a h b a
-- 2012-08-07T10:22:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-07/egypt-libya-agree-on-anti-smuggling-effort-on-border-crossings.html
Egypt ’s Finance Minister Momtaz al-
Saieed agreed with his Libyan counterpart to tighten security
measures at border crossings to combat smuggling, according to a
statement received from the minister’s office by e-mail today.  Libyan Finance Minister Hassan Zilkam, who is visiting his
country’s neighbor, told al-Saieed in a meeting yesterday that
 Libya  is keen on increasing its investment in the Egyptian
market and bolstering economic ties, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Abdel Latif Wahba in Cairo at 
 alatifwahba@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
